<p>GDP growth: 4.0%  GDP: $281bn (PPP: $261bn) Inflation: 2.9% Population: 5.4m GDP per head: $52,220 (PPP: $48,560)</p>

<p>The opposition's performance in the 2011 elections—taking six seats out of 87—may look unimpressive, but it represented a three-fold increase and was based on a 40% share of the vote, so the long-ruling People's Action Party has been warned. It will respond by displaying some interest in popular concerns, but is probably incapable of the fundamental political reform that sooner or later will be required. The economy will weaken a bit as global trade slows.</p>

